parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake line failure can cause loss of brake fluid, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, or even complete brake failure.
symptoms: Brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to stop or has extended stopping distance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake pad wear can cause reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and accidents.
symptoms: Brake pads wear out quickly
brakes make a loud squealing noise
brakes grab or pull to one side
extended stopping distance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the vehicle to lose power steering, making it difficult to control, and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side while braking
the vehicle steers by itself into other traffic lanes
loss of power steering
steering malfunctions
and the vehicle goes to the right unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose power brakes, making it difficult to stop, and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side when the brakes are applied
brake pads and shoes/calipers need to be replaced
and the vehicle experiences intermittent braking malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the diesel fuel system can cause the vehicle to jerk, produce black smoke, and potentially lead to accidents or stall the engine.
symptoms: The vehicle jerks
black smoke comes from the tailpipe
the fuel filter rings blow off
and the vehicle starts pouring fuel onto the highway.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The misalignment of the front end can cause the vehicle to steer by itself into other traffic lanes, making it difficult to control and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle steers by itself into other traffic lanes
and the dealer attributes the issue to front end alignment problems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unwanted ABS brake activation can cause sudden and unexpected braking, which can lead to accidents, loss of control, or rear-end collisions.
symptoms: ABS brake activates without reason
sudden braking
loss of vehicle control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine's failure to decelerate can cause the vehicle to maintain speed, even when the driver takes their foot off the accelerator, which can lead to accidents, loss of control, or difficulty stopping.
symptoms: Engine RPM stays at 2025 for 10 seconds after letting off the accelerator
engine will not decelerate
vehicle maintains speed instead of going into idle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Vehicle surging can cause loss of control, accidents, or difficulty maintaining a steady speed.
symptoms: Vehicle surges while in gear
both in drive and reverse.
